<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="288" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1907" box="[325,467,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Apennocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[325,467,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Apennocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only genus among taxa allied to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[928,1038,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Germalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[928,1038,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Germalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which wing polymorphism and a flightless morph is documented. This condition is associated with habitat permanency in Lygaeoidea (
<bibRefCitation author="Slater, J. A." pageId="3" pageNumber="288" pagination="217 - 229" refId="ref3677" refString="Slater, J. A. (1977) The incidence and evolutionary significance of wing polymorphism in lygaeid bugs with particular reference to those of South Africa. Biotropica, 9 (4), 217 - 229. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2388139" type="journal article" year="1977">Slater 1977</bibRefCitation>
) and relatively common in Afrotopical, Nearctic and Palaearctic representatives of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fallen, 1814" authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1814" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Geocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1250,1353,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Geocoris</emphasis>
Fallén, 1814
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
